  "description": "ADL (Agent Definition Language) is a vendor-neutral, declarative standard for defining AI agents, including their tools, LLM settings, RAG inputs, permissions, and dependencies. It brings consistency, governance, and portability to enterprise AI by providing a clear, machine-readable agent blueprint.",
